1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - This paper is primarily focused on cryptanalysis of a specific cipher, and proposes a new attacking scheme using a parallel genetic algorithm. This category is the most likely fit for this paper. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - Information theory is closely related to cryptography, and this paper may involve some information theoretic concepts. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new algorithmic approach to breaking the MH cipher, which may involve data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The use of metaheuristics and genetic algorithms in particular may fall under this category. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - Genetic algorithms are a type of evolutionary algorithm, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. This category may be relevant if the paper discusses the use of AI techniques in cryptanalysis.
